title: Wall Street Breakfast May 30: What Moved Markets This Week
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description:
This is a revamped roundtable format hosted by Nathaniel E. Baker and featuring:

Aaron Task, VP Contributor Content and co-host Seeking Alpha's Alpha Trader podcast, 

Brad Olesen, VP News

Steve Alpher, Managing Editor News, co-host Alpha Trader

Content Segments (Spotify users can click on the timestamp to link to the start of the segment):

Market wrap-up of the week (1:04)

Recovery in bank stocks (2:54)

Bear market rally? The disconnect with the real economy (4:32)

Seeking Alpha Content That Caught Our Eye This Week (8:46)

Aaron: What If You Prepared For A Bear Market And No One Came? by John Gilluly

Brad: Jenner exposé paints Kylie-Coty deal in unflattering terms

Steve: Trump vs. Twitter war escalates further

Nathaniel: A Few Safe-Haven REITs To Help You Sleep Well At Night, By Brad Thomas

Twitter's stock continues to trail its influence (17:23)

What moved markets this month. Don't sell in May... (18:20)

The "prepper trade" (21:08)

Learn more about your ad choices. Visit megaphone.fm/adchoices
